//- CVE template management: list + delete. Templates are created/updated from
//- the editor's "Configure Defaults" dialog.
extends layout

block content
  .pad2
    h2 CVE templates
    p.tgrey Templates capture which fields show by default and their preset values for new CVEs. Create or update them from the editor's "Configure Defaults" dialog (the cog button), choosing "Me" or a team as the scope.
    table.vtbl.wht
      thead
        tr
          th Name
          th Scope
          th
      tbody
        each t in templates
          tr
            td= t.name
            td
              if t.scope == 'team'
                | team: #{t.team}
              else
                | personal
            td
              form(method="POST", action="/templates/" + t._id + "/delete", onsubmit="return confirm('Delete template " + t.name + "?')")
                input(type="hidden", name="_csrf", value=csrfToken)
                button.fbn.vgi-del(type="submit") Delete
        if !templates || !templates.length
          tr
            td(colspan=3)
              span.sml.tgrey No templates yet — open a CVE, click the gear (Configure Defaults), set your fields, and "Save as template".
